      developmentalNotes: 'At ages three to four, children are building spatial awareness through physical interaction with furniture, climbing over, crawling under, and squeezing between pieces. Furniture worksheets channel this physical spatial knowledge into verbal and visual representations. Fine motor skills benefit from coloring furniture illustrations with multiple straight and curved lines that require controlled hand movements.',
